Breakfast is good, with wide range of meat, cereals, fruits and juices.	Drinks taken in the hotel bar are a pleasure, with friendly bar staff that can mix cocktails and long drinks with skill and a smile; nothing is too much for them.	Breakfast was downstairs in the breakfast room so we had a full bufet not just a limited eat-in version.	If you need a drink, its better to walk next door to the Bar at the Pulitzer, which seems more civilized and lively.	The service was great, the room was made ready and available before check-in time, breakfast was very nice.